description.documentation: Replaces values in the specified columns with nulls. You can choose to use the default list, supply your own, or both.

propertyDescriptions.name: useDefaultNaList
propertyDescriptions.documentation: Use the default list and replace 'null', 'NaN', 'NA', and 'N/A' with null.

propertyDescriptions.name: customNaList
propertyDescriptions.documentation: Provide a comma separated list of values to replace with null.

description.documentation: Replaces null values in a column with the specified replacement value.
Replaces values in a column that match the specified search value.
Clips values so that all values are between the lower and upper boundaries.

propertyDescriptions.name: lower
propertyDescriptions.documentation: All values lower than this value will be set to this value.

propertyDescriptions.name: upper
propertyDescriptions.documentation: All values higher than this value will be set to this value.

propertyDescriptions.name: useValues
propertyDescriptions.documentation: If true, values outside boundaries will be set to the boundary values. If false, those values will be set to null.

description.documentation: Scale values in the column to lie within the specified range (default=[0, 1]).

propertyDescriptions.name: rangeMin
propertyDescriptions.documentation: This will be the minimum value after scaling. Default is 0.

propertyDescriptions.name: rangeMax
propertyDescriptions.documentation: This will be the maximum value after scaling. Default is 1.

propertyDescriptions.name: dataMin
propertyDescriptions.documentation: Minimum value of the data. If none is provided, a scan of the data will be performed to find the minimum.

propertyDescriptions.name: dataMax
propertyDescriptions.documentation: Maximum value of the data. If none is provided, a scan of the data will be performed to find the maximum.
